      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9d68795b861246ed816517caa90487e3">
         <head>JOEL E. SPINGARN (1875-1939)</head>
         <p>Joel Spingarn was an educator and writer who published works on literary criticism and collections of his own poetry. He is most well-known for his involvement in social reform, primarily his work with the NAACP and his establishment of the Spingarn Medal, given to recognize the contributions of African-Americans.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a0d2c934abc14ad66e0e5ff292c9647b">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This finding aid was produced from a previously existing manuscripts inventory. All pertinent information has been retained.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
